            "answer_text": "Taking the following from the \"Non-verbal Categories\" part of a publication on http://www.opsu.edu/Academics/LiberalArts/Speech/files/COMM1113/NONVERBAL.pdf, I would suggest a \"penetrating\" stare would be an example of chronemics in nonverbal communication, as well as a long yawn with a furrowed brow, or a sigh (of boredom perhaps); closing one's arms or legs; positioning the body at a 90 degree angle from the speaker (\"I'm not listeting to you - you're full of it/unimportant\"). NONVERBAL CATEGORIES\u2022Kinesics \u2013 body language\u2022Oculesics [ocalics] \u2013 use of eyes\u2022Proxemics \u2013 use of space\u2022Haptics \u2013 touching behavior\u2022Vocalics [paravocalics or paralanguage] not what you say but HOW you say it ",
